==English==

===Etymology===
:Named after the Irish-born Scottish [[physicist]] [[w:William Thomson, 1st Baron Kelvin|William Thomson, Lord Kelvin]].

===Noun===
'''kelvin''', '''degree Kelvin''' (obsolete)
#In the [[International System of Units]], the [[base unit]] of [[thermodynamic temperature]]; 1/273.16 of the thermodynamic temperature of the [[triple point]] of [[water]].
[[Category:English eponyms]]

====Symbol====
:'''K'''
:''Note: Use of the degree symbol is obsolete.''

